I"†<p>When using KDE 5.18, in order to make your computer turn off its display after locking the screen, do the following.</p>

<p>Go to your <strong>Systems Settings</strong>, and go to the <strong>Notifications</strong> section</p>

<p>Next, in the <strong>Applications</strong>, click on the <em>Configure‚Ä¶</em> button. This will open a dialog of ‚ÄúNotifications -&gt; Application Settings‚Äù</p>

<p>Next, select the <strong>Screen Saver</strong> application, and click on the <em>Configure Events‚Ä¶</em> button.</p>

<p>Next, select the action of your choice (i.e. ‚Äú<em>Screen locked</em>‚Äù), check the box <em>Run command</em>, and then enter the command below. The command below will run as soon as the screen gets locked.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>/bin/sleep 5<span class="p">;</span> /usr/bin/xset dpms force off
</code></pre></div></div>
